"Abstract This and the subsequent article in this issue of The Report are contributed by Christopher Millard and Graham Smith respectively, both of Clifford Chance, Solicitors (London). In the first Chris Millard discusses access to the source code of a computer program in the context of the Insolvency Act 1986. He considers whether a liquidator might, under the Act, defeat the licensees' access claim or other expectations and what steps the license can take to minimise these problems. In the second article Graham Smith considers the position regarding access to source code written specifically for a user that user wish for example to change software house for continued maintenance and development of his system."
